Battery technology has undergone tremendous developments during the last 2 decades. Li-ion cells are now available commercially in the 2170 (or 21700) format, which has a specific energy of 260 Wh/kg while delivering a stable discharge rate of 1C (100% depth-of-discharge (DOD), according to our own experimentation). Historically, the performance of Li-ion chemistry has increased between 5%\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
