				\begin{document}$$30''$$\end{document} pitch) over an 8-metre seating section. Considering a minimal volume for cockpit, cargo (1.7 m3), and systems, the total tube length rose to 14.5 m with a maximum width of 1.8 m and a maximum height of 2.0 m. Due to the mission and propulsion characteristics, the concept rapidly converged into a high-wing, T-tail configuration with four 300 kW-class motors driving large 2.8 m propellers. While a twin-motor configuration would probably be more energy- and weight-efficient, the balanced-field-length requirements with one-engine-inoperative(OEI)\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
